                    <h4>Alchemist Guide</h4>
                    <hr>
                    <div>
                        <article>
<div><span style="font-size: x-large;"><span style="font-size: x-large;"><span style="font-family: 'times new roman';"><span style="color: #00ff14;">Welcome to my Alchemist Guide!</span><br /><br /><span style="color: #ff0014;">Alchemist is a Special Occupation which is found in Elban. <br /><br />You must be level 100 to have access to the quest [The Principle of Alchemy]. Completing this quest will change your occupation, so do understand the consequences!</span><br /><span style="color: #0047ff;"><br />The Alchemist profession was found in an Ancient Document. Alchemists can create anything from nothing using the knowledge they have and secret energy (SOURCE: VAFARDO)<br /></span><br /><span style="color: #0047ff;">Alchemists are a class that uses their catalysts created from either production or brought from the fellow Alchemist, Vafardo, to deal damage against monsters by the power of ailments and spells. Overall I think they serve best as the <strong>Damage Role/Front Line Support, but this does not mean they can play other roles too.</strong><br /><br /></span><span style="color: #00ff14;">That being out of the way, lets go through what this guide covers!<br /><br /></span></span></span></span>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;">Skill Descriptions and Guide on Order of Using the Skills</span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler">(Source:&nbsp;@yuhee 's <a style="color: #ff00eb;" href="http://irunaonline.boards.net/thread/27429/alchemist-skills-acquisition-description" target="_blank" rel="noopener norewrite">Alchemist Skills Thread.</a><span style="color: #ff00eb;">)</span><br /><strong><span style="color: #19e621;">Drain (Active)</span><br /></strong><span style="color: #0047ff;">A dark element magic attack with a chance of absorbing damage you deal to foes.</span><br /><u><span style="color: #ff0014;"><strong>SLv1 - Obtained through the occupation change.</strong></span></u><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #00ff14;">Reflection (Active)</span><br /></strong><span style="color: #0047ff;">A dark element magic attack with a chance to deflecting damage back to your foe.</span><br /><u><span style="color: #ff0014;"><strong>SLv1 - Obtained through the occupation change.</strong></span></u><br /><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #886700;">Mana Mastery (Passive)</span><br /></strong><span style="color: #0047ff;">A book of magic tactics that raises MATK.<br /></span><strong><u><span style="color: #ff0014;">SLv5 - Obtained through the occupation change.</span></u></strong><br /><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #886700;">Enchant (Passive)</span><br /></strong><span style="color: #0047ff;">Adds a bonus to your ATK based on your INT</span><br /><u><span style="color: #ff0014;"><strong>SLv1 - Obtained through the occupation change.</strong></span></u><br /><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #00ff14;">Magic Barrier (Active)</span><br /></strong><span style="color: #0047ff;">Raises target's defense based on their INT</span><br /><u><span style="color: #ff0014;"><strong>SLv2 - Obtained through the occupation change.</strong></span></u><br /><br /><span style="color: #886700;"><br /></span><strong><span style="color: #886700;">Cast Barrier (Passive)</span><br /></strong><span style="color: #0047ff;">Reduce the damage taken while casting a spell.<br /></span><strong><u><span style="color: #ff0014;">SLv1 - Obtained through the occupation change.</span></u></strong><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #886700;">Craft Technique (Passive)</span><br /></strong><span style="color: #0047ff;">Available for Production. The effect depends on Lv.</span><br /><u><span style="color: #ff0014;"><strong>SLv1 - Obtained through the occupation change.<br />SLv2 - Obtained by a Skill Book given by Vafardo. (Lv.160)<br />SLv3 - Obtained by a Skill Book given by Vafardo. (Lv.220)<br />SLv4 - Obtained by a Skill Book given by Vafardo. (Lv.280)</strong></span></u><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #00ff14;">Killer Throw (Active)</span><br /></strong><span style="color: #0047ff;">Throw Killer stick with full force. Available on other allies' enemy. Valid on high-defense target. (The damage can be increased based on your Carpentry Level in Production.) (Requires 1 Killer Stick)</span><br /><span style="font-family: 'times new roman';"><u><span style="color: #ff0014;"><strong>SLv1 - Obtained through the occupation change.<br />SLv2 - Obtained by a Skill Book given by Vafardo. (Lv.140)<br />SLv3 - Obtained by a Skill Book given by Vafardo. (Lv.180)<br />SLv4 - Obtained by a Skill Book given by Vafardo. (Lv.240)</strong></span></u><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #00ff14;">Mana Bullet (Active)</span></strong><br /><span style="color: #0047ff;">Gather magic and shoot it. Neutral element magic.</span><br /><strong><span style="color: #ff0014;"><u>SLv1 -&nbsp;Obtained by a Skill Book given by Vafardo. (Lv.100)<br />SLv2 - Obtained by a Skill Book given by Vafardo. (Lv.160)<br />SLv3 - Obtained by a Skill Book given by Vafardo. (Lv.220)<br />SLv4 - Obtained by a Skill Book given by Vafardo. (Lv.280)</u><br /></span></strong><br /><strong><span style="color: #00ff14;">Bloom Blizzard (Active)</span></strong><br /><span style="color: #0047ff;">Generate blizzard with Ice flower. Hits multiple times and freeze foes. Damage and consumption based on Lv. (The consumption is fixed to 1.) (Lowers damage per target. 1 Target = 100% Damage, 2 Targets = 80-90% Damage and 3 Targets = 60-70% Damage.) (Requires 1 Ice Flower)</span><br /><u><strong><span style="color: #ff0014;">SLv1 - Obtained by a quest given by Vafardo. (Lv.140)</span></strong></u><br /><span style="color: #a9b803;">- Slay: Polpo x 20 (Haufen Harbor)<br />- Slay: Squalo x 20 (Haufen Harbor)<br />- Collect: Water Bead x 5<br />- Collect: Blue Gem x 5 (Chasing Lv.15 (25))</span><br /><strong><span style="color: #ff0014;"><u>SLv2 -&nbsp;Obtained by a Skill Book given by Vafardo. (Lv.200)<br /></u><u>SLv3 - Obtained by a quest given by Vafardo. (Lv.260)</u></span></strong><br /><span style="color: #a9b803;">- Slay: Sirene x 40 (Brienne Mountain)<br />- Slay: Saw Otter x 40 (Brienne Mountain)<br />- Slay: Lont Mantis x 40 (Hashiba Valley)<br />- Slay: Gadave x 1 (Hashiba Valley)</span><br /><u><strong><span style="color: #ff0014;">SLv4 - Obtained by Vafardo (Lv.320) </span></strong><br /><span style="color: #00ff14;"><br /></span></u><strong><span style="color: #00ff14;">Venom Bomb (Active)</span><br /></strong><span style="color: #0047ff;">Attack an enemy with Poison Bomb. 100% chance to poison it. (The ailment damage can be increased based on your Alchemy Level in Production.) (Damage ticks every 3 seconds for 30 seconds.) (Requires 1 Poison Bomb)</span><br /><u><span style="color: #ff0014;"><strong>SLv1 -&nbsp;Obtained by a quest given by Vafardo. (Lv.140)</strong></span><br /></u><span style="color: #a9b803;">- Collect: Dark Bead x 5<br />- Collect: Insect Scale x 20 (Schmets, Inneban Ruins)<br />- Collect: Digestive Juice x 10 (Morays, Inneban Ruins)<br />- Collect: Tarante's Claw x 2 (Tarante, Labilans Sector)</span><br /><u><span style="color: #ff0014;"><strong>SLv2 - Obtained by a Skill Book given by Vafardo. (Lv.180)<br />SLv3 - Obtained by a Skill Book given by Vafardo. (Lv.220)<br />SLv4 - Obtained by a Skill Book given by Vafardo. (Lv.260)</strong><br /></span><span style="color: #00ff14;"><br /></span></u><strong><span style="color: #00ff14;">Meteor Impact (Active)</span><br /></strong><span style="color: #0047ff;">Calls a meteor using Star Bead. Attack and burns enemies in an area. Damage and consumption based on Lv. (The consumption is fixed to 1.) (The ailment damage can be increased based on your Smithing Level in Production.) (Damage ticks every 6 seconds for 60 seconds.) (Spell Cast lowers damage per target. 1 Target = 100% Damage, 2 Targets = 80-90% Damage and 3 Targets = 60-70% Damage.) (Requires 1 Star Bead)</span><br /><u><strong><span style="color: #ff0014;">SLv1 - Obtained by a quest given by Vafardo. (Lv.160)</span></strong><br /></u><span style="color: #a9b803;">- Slay: Metalbrow x 1 (Algaotte Prison)<br />- Slay: Zimov x 1 (Dierolt)<br />- Slay: Kyon x 30 (Algaotte Prison)<br />- Slay: Talpa x 30 (Dierolt)</span><br /><u><strong><span style="color: #ff0014;">SLv2 - Obtained by a Skill Book given by Vafardo. (Lv.200)<br />SLv3 - Obtained by a quest given by Vafardo. (Lv.280)</span></strong><br /></u><span style="color: #a9b803;">- Slay: Mame Danuki x 40 (Kakeula Rift)<br />- Slay: Margot x 40 (Baliki Forest)<br />- Slay: Luberra x 40 (Baliki Forest)<br />- Slay: Sakimori no Ryu x 1 (Mt.Ochikubo)</span><br /><u><strong><span style="color: #ff0014;">SLv4 - Obtained by Vafardo. (Lv.340) </span></strong></u><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #00ff14;">Throw Revita (Active)</span><br /></strong><span style="color: #0047ff;">Recover HP by Revita (Throw). Can throw it to an ally. Cannot revive an ally. (Requires 1 Revita (Throw)).</span><br /><u><strong><span style="color: #ff0014;">SLv1 - Obtained by a Skill Quest given by Vafardo. (Lv.160)</span></strong></u><br /><span style="color: #a9b803;">- Collect: Bead Fragment x 5<br />- Collect: Clear Jelly x 5 (Flukes in Grolg Mountains)<br />- Collect: Large Leaf x 30 (Colon Tree in Starfall Road)<br />- Collect: Silk Thread x 30 (Albums in Labilans Sector)</span><br /><u><strong><span style="color: #ff0014;">SLv2 - Obtained by a Skill Quest given by Vafardo. (Lv.240)</span></strong></u><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #886700;">Potion Technique (Passive)</span><br /></strong><span style="color: #0047ff;">Increases the healing amount of HP/MP Items.</span><br /><u><strong><span style="color: #ff0014;">SLv1 - Obtained by a Skill Quest given by Vafardo. (Lv.180)</span></strong><br /></u><span style="color: #a9b803;">- Collect: Light Jewel x 1 (Alchemy Lv.65(75))<br />- Collect: Ether x 5<br />- Collect: Spirit Shard x 30 (Elemental Spirits in Divine Tower)<br />- Collect: Life Bead x 1 (Made by Rulea the Merchant in Elban by Synthesis)</span><br /><u><strong><span style="color: #ff0014;">SLv2 - Obtained by a Skill Book given by Vafardo. (Lv.260)</span></strong><br /></u><br /><strong><span style="color: #886700;">Efficiency (Passive)</span><br /></strong><span style="color: #0047ff;">A technique to enhance efficiency. Delay decreases based on Lv.</span><br /><u><strong><span style="color: #ff0014;">SLv1 - Obtained by a Skill Quest given by Vafardo. (Lv.200)</span></strong><br /></u><span style="color: #a9b803;">-Slay: Magonza x 1 (Magonza Fortress)<br />-Slay: Beelzedam x 1 (Ruins of Zamani)<br />-Slay: Kefer x 30 (Mt.Jimuy)<br />-Slay: Cuppebite x 30 (Frontline Base)</span><br /><u><strong><span style="color: #ff0014;">SLv2 - Obtained by a Skill Quest given by Vafardo. (Lv.240)</span></strong><br /></u><span style="color: #a9b803;">-Collect: E Tablet x 1 (Alchemy Lv.115(125))</span><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #00ff14;">Haze Revita (Active)</span><br /></strong><span style="color: #0047ff;">Recover HP with Powder Revita. Heal allies around you. The range gets wider based on Lv. (SLv1 heals 20% of your MaxHP, SLv2 heals 22%. Can be increased by 1% every 60 levels earned in Production.)</span><br /><u><strong><span style="color: #ff0014;">SLv1 - Obtained by a Skill Quest given by Vafardo. (Lv.220)</span></strong><br /></u><span style="color: #a9b803;">-Slay: Ziddu x 1 (Mubele Pass)<br />-Slay: Floral Mantis x 30 (Agano Pass)<br />-Collect: Sage Stone x 1 (Alchemy Lv.85(95))<br />-Collect: Mysterious Jelly x 30 (Igniz, Fort Slebinus)</span><br /><u><strong><span style="color: #ff0014;">SLv2 - Obtained by a Skill Book given by Vafardo. (Lv.300)</span></strong></u><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #00ff14;">Bloody Throw (Active)</span><br /></strong><span style="color: #0047ff;">A throwing technique to make an enemy bleed. Increases critical damage. (Killer Throw can now cause the Bleeding Ailment on enemies with this skill.)</span><br /><u><strong><span style="color: #ff0014;">SLv1 - Obtained by a Skill Quest given by Vafardo. (Lv.240) (Lasts two minutes.)</span></strong><br /></u><span style="color: #a9b803;">-Slay: Ganaph x 40 (Guevol's Fortress)<br />-Slay: Layve x 40 (Kimale's Fortress)<br />-Slay: Milestie x 40 (Maze of Umberto [EP2])<br />-Slay: Gerust x 1 (Kimale's Fortress)</span><br /><u><strong><span style="color: #ff0014;">SLv2 - Obtained by a Skill Book given by Vafardo. (Lv.300) (Lasts three minutes.)</span></strong></u><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #886700;">Poison Mastery (Passive)</span><br /></strong><span style="color: #0047ff;">Knowledge of how to increase poison. Ailment damage and duration except K.O increase. (All ailments damage and duration caused by Alchemist except for Drain increases. This does not work for other player's ailments.)</span><br /><u><strong><span style="color: #ff0014;">SLv1 - Obtained by a Skill Quest given by Vafardo. (Lv.260)</span></strong></u><br /><span style="color: #a9b803;">-Collect: Greenish Meat x 40 (Neknotts, Magonza Fortress)<br />-Collect: Lavender Fur x 40 (Koboks, Maze of Umberto [EP2])<br />-Collect: Spiny Vine x 40 (Natra Keepers, Mawid Plains)<br />-Collect: Dragon Scale x 1 (Guevol, Guevol's Fortress)</span><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #00ff14;">Cursed Rain (Active)</span><br /></strong><span style="color: #0047ff;">Generate cursed rain with Cursed Rosary. Deals damage at a fix interval. (Damage ticks every 3 seconds for 30 seconds. There is cast involved. It is a dark element spell. Requires 1 Cursed Rosary.)</span><br /><u><strong><span style="color: #ff0014;">SLv1 - Obtained by a Skill Quest given by Vafardo. (Lv.280)</span></strong><br /></u><span style="color: #a9b803;">Collect:<br />- Cursed Evil Eye x 10 (Lytic Jellies, Tower of Yafula)<br />- Eternal Grudge x 5&nbsp;(Ghosts in Abbey Ruin/Cianshis in Mira Abyss)</span><br /><span style="color: #a9b803;">Slay:<br />- Gatekeeper Beelzem x 40 (Primordial Lands)<br />- Xeltysis x 1 (Primordial Lands)</span><br /><span style="color: #ff0014;"><u><strong>SLv2 - Obtained by Vafardo. (Lv.340) </strong></u><br /></span><br /><strong><span style="color: #00ff14;">Accelerate (Active)</span></strong><br /><span style="color: #0047ff;">Move fast using stamina and magic energy. Decrease MaxHP &amp; MP and make movement &amp; attack speed faster. (MaxHP&amp;MP-5%, ASPD+20%, CSPD+5%, Movement Speed+?%, lasts two minutes.)</span><br /><u><strong><span style="color: #ff0014;">SLv1 - Obtained by a Skill Quest given by Vafardo. (Lv.300)</span></strong><br /></u><span style="color: #a9b803;">You have a test which is pretty easy, you have to bring an item to King Elbano within two minutes to complete the test. You are then awarded Accelerate upon turning it in to Vafardo.</span><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #886700;">Meister (Passive)</span></strong><br /><span style="color: #0047ff;">Proof that the result of your training was recognized. For recipes where Production Lv. is significantly lower, restrictions on batch production become unrestricted. (Strengthening equipment and making equipment can now be batch produced if they are &lt;=10 levels from your production level.)</span><br /><u><strong><span style="color: #ff0014;">SLv1 - Obtained by a Skill Quest given by Vafardo. (Lv.300)</span></strong><br /></u><span style="color: #a9b803;">Collect ANY ONE of the following (beware, it will be taken away when giving it to Vafardo):<br />- Smithing Charm x 1 (Smithing Lv.115(125))<br />- Carpentry Charm x 1 (Carpentry Lv.115(125))<br />- Tailoring Charm x 1 (Tailoring Lv.115(125))<br />- Alchemy Charm x 1 (Alchemy Lv.115(125))<br />- Chasing Charm x 1 (Chasing Lv.115(125))<br />- Cooking Charm x 1 (Cooking Lv.115(125))</span><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #00ff14;">Smog (Active)</span></strong><br /><span style="color: #0047ff;">Generate harmful smoke with smog balls. Ensure paralysis and blinding of enemies. (Uses 1 Smog Ball, can be bought from Vafardo's Catalyst Shop or made in Alchemy Production Lv.150-190.)</span><br /><u><strong><span style="color: #ff0014;">SLv1 - Obtained by a Skill Quest given by Vafardo. (Lv.320)</span></strong></u><br /><span style="color: #a9b803;">Slay:<br />- Veleno Rosa x 1 (Forisco Plains South)<br />- Cochlea x 30 (Mount Nachberg)<br />- Solonia x 30 (Fundamental Globe)<br />- Bizon x 30 (Ibrie Palace)</span><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #00ff14;">Summon the Workshop (Active)</span></strong><br /><span style="color: #0047ff;">Summon the studio specializing in production. When producing in the workshop, you can receive various benefits. <br />(Consumes all of your MP)</span><br /><u><strong><span style="color: #ff0014;">SLv1 - Obtained by a Skill Quest given by Vafardo. (Lv.340) (Lasts two minutes.)</span></strong></u><br /><span style="font-size: x-large;"><span style="font-family: 'times new roman';"><span style="color: #a9b803;">Collect:<br />- Magic Crystal x 10 (Chasing Lv.120(130))<br />- Mysterious Gold Coin x 60 (Lizard Reapers, Fossa Flatlands)<br /></span><br /><strong><span style="color: #00ff14;">Grief Chain (Active)</span></strong><br /><span style="color: #0047ff;">The secret to turn the enemy's grief into power. The secret that the power changes depending on the number of ailments occurring in the enemy.&nbsp;</span><br /><u><strong><span style="color: #ff0014;">SLv1 - Obtained by a Skill Quest given by Vafardo. (Lv 340)</span></strong></u><br /><span style="color: #a9b803;">Slay:<br />- Ster x 1 (Mount Nachberg)<br />- Evil Dragon Leviam x 1 (Imperial Palace)<br />- Hammer Scorpion x 30 (Weffel Tower)<br />- Fox Priest x 30 (Achitem Training Stairs)</span><br /><br /><span style="color: #03a2b8;">In battle against bosses, I would use the skills in the following order:<br /><strong><u>Smog or Drain - Drain or Smog - Kill Throw - Venom Bomb - Meteor Impact - Cursed Rain - Mana Bullet - Bloom Blizzard - MATK Set - Grief Chain - Support/Switch Set to Poison/Burn Set.<br /></u></strong>This skill chain is best for survivability. However, if you are looking to get quick damage output, then you could follow this:<br /><strong><u>Smog - Venom Bomb - Meteor Impact - Cursed Rain - Kill Throw - Smog - Drain - Mana Bullet - MATK Set - Bloom Blizzard - Grief Chain Set - Grief Chain - Swap to Poison/Burn Set.<br /></u></strong>Of course, in the end it all comes down to your playstyle, and the bosses can change this up greatly as well.<br />All skill books come to a grand total of 88.1 million spina.</span></span></span></span></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;">Pros/Cons</span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><span style="font-family: 'times new roman'; font-size: x-large;"><strong><u><span style="color: #00ff14;">Pros</span></u></strong><br /><span style="color: #03a2b8;">-Alchemists can heal for high amounts with Haze Revita, meaning they can play the Healer Role pretty well.<br />-Alchemists can surpass defence&nbsp;barriers with their ailments, excluding Cursed Rain/Bloom Blizzard (Spell Cast)/Meteor Impact(Spell Cast)<br />-Alchemists have extra production success which is a notable difference in production, also to include Meister and Production Workshop, some people doing production might want to reconsider...<br />-All of the skills which require the consumption of an item will only consume 1 MP.<br />-Alchemists can MP Heal.<br />-Alchemists share the Magic Barrier buff with Enchanters and also Reflect with the Wizard tree which can help out with defence and also damage output.<br />-Alchemists have a range of AoE attack skills that deal high damage, the best of them being Cursed Rain as it delivers high damage to all mobs (does not lower damage depending on the amount of mobs) and also has the widest range.</span><br /><u style="font-weight: bold;"><span style="color: #ff0014;">Cons</span></u><br /><span style="color: #8a5902;">-Some bosses have immunity to ailments which could kill part of an Alchemist's purpose.<br />-Meteor Impact, Cursed Rain, and Accelerate have a high cast demand (Unsure for Accelerate, but Meteor Impact and Cursed Rain is 850 CSPD?)<br />-You must have Smithing, Carpentry, and Alchemy to a high level in production to get a significant difference in Ailment damage. You also will need high level productions overall to get more Haze Revita healing.<br />-The total cost to buy all skills by books is 88.1m spina, and you will find yourself lots of times visiting the catalyst shop to buy pots. Alchemist is an expensive class.<br /></span><br /></span></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;">Vafardo's Shop</span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><span style="color: #03a2b8;">You can purchase catalysts from Vafardo. Here are the prices:<br />Revita (Throw) - 1,000s<br />Killer Stick - 1,500s<br />Powder Revita - 2,500s<br />Star Bead - 5,000s<br />Ice Flower - 5,000s<br />Poison Bomb - 5,000s<br />Cursed Rosary - 5,000s<br />Smog Ball - 5,000s</span></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;">Catalyst Recipes</span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><span style="font-family: 'times new roman';"><span style="font-size: x-large;"><span style="color: #ff00eb;">There are catalyst recipes you can make inside of production if you are tight on a budget but have high production. The following recipes are what you will find in each Production Tree:<br /><span style="color: #ff0014;">Smithing - Star Beads From Lv.10 - 100.<br />Carpentry - Killer Sticks from Lv.5 - 95.<br />Chasing - Ice Flowers from Lv.10 - 100.<br />Alchemy - Revita (Throw) from Lv.1 - 91, Powder Revita from Lv.10 - 100, Poison Bomb from Lv.5 - 95, Cursed Rosary from Lv.80 - 130 and Smog Ball from Lv.150 - 190.<br /><span style="color: #03a2b8;">You can find the recipes for them <a href="http://www.iruna-online.info/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">here.</a></span></span></span></span></span></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;">Stat Builds</span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><span style="font-family: 'times new roman';"><span style="font-size: x-large;"><span style="color: #03a2b8;">Here are some builds you can go for:</span><br /><strong><u><span style="color: #a9b803;">Build #1 (Main Alchemist Build)</span></u></strong><span style="color: #a9b803;"> -</span><span style="color: #03a2b8;">Involves investing stats into INT/VIT/DEX/GL/BL or EXP. Boosts your MATK and also helps with the damage for ailments too. You also can specialise in Alchemy, Carpentry and Chasing with this build. You have a high amount of HP and MP, and also a decent amount of DEF and MDEF.<br /></span><br /><span style="color: #a9b803;"><strong><u>Build #2 (The Production Build)</u></strong> -</span><span style="color: #03a2b8;">Involves investing stats into STR/INT/VIT/AGI/DEX/CRT (256 into every stat and any spare stats you decide to invest into.). You specialise in all productions and have a decent amount of production success in every area. This may however, come to the cost of dealing extra damage by ailments or spell casts.</span></span></span></div>
<span style="font-family: 'times new roman'; font-size: x-large;"><span style="font-family: 'times new roman'; font-size: x-large;"><span style="font-family: 'times new roman'; font-size: x-large;"><span style="color: #ff00eb;"><span style="font-size: x-large;"><span style="font-size: x-large;"><span style="font-size: x-large;"><span style="font-family: 'times new roman';"><span style="color: #03a2b8;">There is tons of equipment you can use as an Alchemist. Here I will organise them into sets: (Source = <a href="http://www.iruna-online.info/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">Iruna Online Info</a>&nbsp;)</span><br /></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;">Cast Set</span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><span style="color: #a684ff;"><strong><u>Cast Set</u></strong> - This set focuses on trying to get those Ailments on as quickly as possible for the most damage output. It is additionally great for getting the cast down for Haze Revita for playing the Healer role. Here are the equips I would recommend:<br /><strong>Weapons</strong><br />Caduceus III - MATK+18%, Cast Time-30% Melee R+3% Critical damage-10% HP Absorb by chance.<br />Sauro Stick L6 - MATK+20%, Magic Pierce+14%, Cast Time-20%, INT+10, DEX+10, MP Cost-20%, All Magic +4%<br />General Wand III - Fire &amp; Water &amp; Wind &amp; Earth magic+14%, ATK-25%, Cast Time-24%, Skill Delay -0.5sec, Magic attack chance by attack<br />Spell Book Vol.4 - MATK+10%, INT+12, DEX+8, Neutral Magic+20% Cast Time-25%<br />Eventail III -&nbsp;Melee to Neutral +30%, Cast Time -50%, Small counter chance up by AGI, Magic evasion +5%, Twice attack chance<br /><br /><strong>Body Equipment</strong><br />Altoshear (Strengthened x 3) - MATK+10%, Cast time-35%, Melee R+8%, Autoskill+8%, Range Cut+4%<br />Emido (Strengthened x 2) - MATK+16%, Absolute evasion+10%, Cast time-25%, Autoskills+10%, Spellburst+12%, magic+1%, Magic R-25%<br />Weiss (Strengthened x 3) - All Stats+8, ATK&middot;MATK+4%, Absolute evasion+3%, MaxHP+5%, Cast time-10%, Spell Burst+5%<br /><br /><strong>Additional Equipment</strong><br />Clematis (Strengthened x 1) - MATK+8%, Skill delay-1.5sec, Cast time-20%, MP cost-20%, If Lv&lt;300, MP Cost+50%.<br />Lobelia Hood - MATK+5%, MaxMP-30%, MP Cost+20%, Cast Time-30%, Spell Burst +5%, Skill Delay-1.5sec<br />Miselatis (Strengthened x 1) - Heal Reward+1500&amp;+5%, DEX+10, Auto Recovery+15%, Cast Time-20%, Delay-1.2sec if INT&gt;249<br />Montol Colliet (Strengthened x 2) - ASPD+30%, Cast time-20%, Fainted Time-1 sec, Paralysis Time-1 sec, Ignition Time-3 sec If Lv&gt;300, Delay-1.5sec<br /><br /><strong>Special Equipment</strong><br />Spell King's Ring - INT+10, Cast Time-20%, Magic+300. If Lv300 or more, MATK+8% (Hidden: All Magic+10% if specific conditions are met.)<br />Mage Ring - MATK+4% if Lv&gt;255, Cast Time-16%.<br />Mage Necklace - Magic R+2%, Neutral R+3%, Cast time-15% if INT&gt;149<br /><br /><strong>Crystas</strong><br />Gerust - MATK+15%, Skill Delay+1sec, Adds MATK +5% on Weapons<br />Sauro II - MaxHP +20%, MaxMP +20%, Exp +5%. On weapon, ATK +15%, MATK +20%, Melee pierce +5%, Magic pierce +5%<br />Beelzetor - MATK +10% When MP equipped consumption +35% in weapons, further MATK +4% Absolute accuracy +25%<br />Fiona - Magic pierce +3%, MaxMP +10%, Adds MATK +14% Delay -0.3 sec on Weapons.<br />Isurugi - MATK +15%, MP cost +50%, Adds MP cost -25% and MATK -3% on Weapons.<br />Moldus - DEX+1, Adds MATK+7% on Armors. Double effect if DEX &gt; 199.<br />Fred - MaxMP + 5%, When equipped on Armors, MATK + 25 MATK + 18%<br />Medona - MATK +6% Skill delay -0.1 sec, Cast time -15% MaxHP and MaxMP -8% And when equipped with body, further MATK +10%<br />Dunkelis II - MATK +15%, Magic pierce +5% Adds MATK +5%, Magic up by Lv, Magic pierce +5% on Additional.<br />Tarna - MATK +10% Magic +100, Adds MATK 5% and Magic +400 on Additional.<br />Ushilth - Spell burst +1%. Skill delay -0.2 sec. Adds Skill delay -0.3s and MATK +12% on Additional.<br />Agira Jarma - MATK +12% Cast defense +5%, adds MATK +8% INT +5 if equipped on Special.<br />Mezzaluna - MATK +15% MaxMP -40%, Adds MaxMP +40% on Special.<br /><br /><strong>Al Crystas</strong><br />Bergen - MATK +3% ATK -3%, Magic evasion +2%<br />Douin - MATK +2% Melee R +2%, Heal recovery +5%<br />Zazel - ATK +15 ATK +2% MATK +30 MATK +2%<br />Vida - ATK +8%, MATK +8%, Autoskills -5%, Melee R -20%, Magic R -20%<br />Jusal - MATK +4% Water magic +4% Cast time -4%<br />Fiona (UNRELEASED) - MATK + 4% Magic Pierce + 5% MaxMP + 7%<br />Seele Zauga II (UNRELEASED) - MATK +5% Spell burst +3% MaxMP +3% Melee R -25%<br />Parazaia - MATK +20 MATK +3% Auto MP recovery +25%<br />Ouvel - ATK +6% MATK +6% MaxHP -10% MaxMP -10%<br /><br />Pure Red Lines, Blue lines and Cyan lines is what I would recommend for this set.<br /><br /><strong>Relic Crystas</strong><br />Cast Time -1%<br />Debby -&nbsp;MATK +2%, Rate cut +2%<br />MATK+1<br />Memory Fragment -&nbsp;ATK&amp;MATK +10, DEF&amp;MDEF +10, MaxHP&amp;MP +10<br />Rita -&nbsp;Small MATK up by level. During White Day, small MATK up by VIT.<br />Uradoom -&nbsp;ATK&amp;MATK +5, ATK&amp;MATK +1%<br />Magic +1%<br /><br /><strong>Abilities - Only Fluency Lv1, if you find that every cast is fast before you have fluency on all your equipment you can try for Magic Lv5 on equipment.</strong></span></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;">Poison Set</span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><span style="color: #93ff84;"><strong><u>Poison Set</u></strong> - This set focuses on getting that extra poison damage, which is probably the most helpful in game in terms of additional ailment damage.<br /><strong>Weapons</strong><br />Le Feu Kai II - VIT +10, Item Delay-1.2sec, Melee Pierce +5%, Poison Dmg+20%, HP Recovery chance by defense.<br />Sepscorne -&nbsp;Poison dmg +20%, AGI +5, MaxMP +100, Poison yourself chance by attack.<br />Ceduro II - Magic R -10%, DEX+8 Autoskill+12% ATK up based on Lv. Poison Dmg +25% Critical up, Ailment R +10%.<br />Poisoned Knife - DEX +1 Poison +15%, Critical rate +30.<br />Alacran III -&nbsp;Water attribute, Evasion +15%, Absolute evasion +8%, Magic R -20%, Additional Attack chance by Attack. (Hidden: Poison Dmg+30%, if Monk, Autoskill+10%.)<br /><br /><strong>Body Equipment</strong><br />Thief Garb (Strengthened x 3) - Evasion +6%, Magic Evasion +6%, Critical rate +15, Poison dmg +10%.<br /><br /><strong>Additional Equipment</strong><br />Blume Gift - Poison dmg +10%, Critical up, Self Poison chance by attack.<br /><br /><strong>Special Equipment</strong><br />Bud Ring - Poison dmg +3%, MP Cost -15%, Auto HP Recovery -20%.<br />Any 2 slot spec will also do with 2 chosen Crystas below.<br /><br /><strong>Crystas</strong><br />Seele Zauga - MaxMP +15%, Poison dmg +15%<br />Veleno Rosa - Poison +10% Delay -0.1 sec. Additional attack chance. Dmg up if poisoned. (Consumes autoskill)<br />Miasma (UNRELEASED) - Poison, Bleed and Burn Dmg+10%.<br /><br /><strong>Relic Crystas</strong><br />Poison Damage +1%<br />Burn Damage +1%<br />Bleed Damage +1%<br /><br /><strong>Al Crystas</strong><br />Magonza (UNRELEASED) - Melee +400, Poison dmg +30%, Paralyze time -1s, Burn time -1s<br /><br />Use the color mixing in any way you'd like, but I recommend either pure red lines, blue lines or cyan lines (blue and green) as these would be pretty helpful to the set whilst just standing dealing poison damage and you can benefit from more HP and defense, more MP and magic defense or more MATK and magic pierce in relations to Cursed Rain.<br /><br /><strong>Abilities</strong><br />Try for Intelligence and Dexterity, as these abilities will have an increase throughout the formula.</span></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;">Resistance Set</span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><span style="color: #8d293d;"><strong><u>Resistance Set</u></strong> - This set focuses on more chances of survival whilst putting on ailments. It comes at the sacrifice of Cast Time and some MATK, but the ailment damage rarely changes from this, making this a great set to carry around for boss fights/farming!<br /><strong>Weapons</strong><br />El Avenir - INT +7 MaxHP +3000 Accuracy +30, Magic Pierce +12%, Melee R +16%.<br />Barotas - Small Magic pierce up by Lv if Lv &gt; 299. HP Recovery chance by defense, MATK +20%, Skill delay -1 sec.<br />Caduceus III - MATK+18%, Cast Time-30% Melee R+3% Critical damage-10% HP Absorb by chance.<br />Genius - Special Sword MaxHP +30% Rate Cut +10% Melee &amp; Magic R+15% Counterattack chance by defense. (Cancel damage when counterattack activates)<br />Barotas -&nbsp;Small Magic pierce up by Lv if Lv &gt; 299. HP regen chance by defense, MATK +20%, Skill delay -1 sec (hidden performance: during defense, probability of HP recovery for 10 sec, Heal = (Lv +45) &times; 11 times)<br />Throat Knife -&nbsp;MATK +20%, Cast defense +15%, Hate rise -10% Autoskill +10%, Magic evasion +5%, Magic counterattack by defense. (Hidden: If Mage Tree Job then Melee&amp;Magic R+10%, Fire&amp;Neutral Magic+10%. Hidden #2: MP Recovery chance by Defense)<br /><br /><strong>Body Equipment</strong><br />Timorier - MATK +8%, Delay -0.5 sec, Melee R +5%, Rate cut +12%.<br />Bellow of Order - Melee and Magic R +12%, ATK up by STR, MATK up by INT, Skill delay -1 sec, Damage cut chance by defense<br />Altoshear (Strengthened x 3) - MATK +10%, Cast time -35%, Melee R +8%, Autoskill +8% Range cut +4%<br />Iron Armor (Strengthened x 3) - MaxHP +4000, Auto HP recovery +24%, KO Time-1.5sec, Melee R +10%.<br />Licht Armor (Strengthened x 3) (UNRELEASED STRENGTHEN X 3) - DEF up by Lv, MDEF up by Lv, Melee R +14%, Magic R +14% Delay -1.2 sec, MaxHP +10%, Skill Delay Reduction chance by Defense.<br />Plate Armor (Strengthened x 3) - VIT +12, Melee R+ 10%, Rate cut +10%, KO time -1 sec, Damage cut chance by defense.<br />Deceiver (Strengthened) -&nbsp;Critical rate -10%, MP cost -17%, MDEF +14%, VIT +10, MaxHP +16%, Rate cut +17%. (Hidden: If Lv&gt;300, Small Melee R up by VIT and Small Magic R up by INT. (0.02 per VIT/INT))<br /><br /><strong>Additional Equipment</strong><br />Sieger Plate - VIT +24, INT +18, Melee R +10%, Magic R +10%, Damage cut +5% during Stun. Ailment R +10%.<br />Idealsol - MaxHP +20% Melee R +5%, Fire R -20%, Damage cut chance by defense, DEF up by Lv.<br />Hydrangea Flower - MaxHP +30%, Melee R +15%, Delay +1.5 sec, Ailment R-50%.<br /><br /><strong>Special Equipment</strong><br />Douin's Feathers - Melee R +5%, Magic R +3%, Heal Reward +10%.<br />Fortitude Ring - Melee R +5%, Magic R +5%, Rate cut +5%, HP recovery if HP is 25% or lower when attacked.<br />Lowell Wristband - MaxHP +10%, Melee R +10%, Magic R -10%, Adds Heal reward +5%, Melee R +5%, Magic R +5% if DEX &gt; 255.<br />Scholar Ring - Magic R +10% if VIT &gt; 199. Melee R +10% if INT &gt; 199.<br /><br /><strong>Crystas</strong><br />Iniliba - Damage cut chance by defense, ATK +10% on Armor, MATK +10% on Armor (Consumes autoskill) (Hidden: Melee &amp; Magic R+10%. Melee and Magic Power up by Lv.)<br />Rogelio - VIT +5, Melee R +4%, MDEF +5%, Hate Rise +10%, Heal Reward +8%, Ailment R +7%.<br />Morbeelzem - Melee R +5%, Magic R +5%, Rate cut +5%, Item recovery -15%<br />Beelzetor - MATK +10%, MP Cost+35%. When put on Weapon, further MATK +4%, Absolute accuracy +25%.<br />Sauro II - MaxHP +20%, MaxMP +20%, Exp +5%. On weapon, ATK +15%, MATK +20%, Melee pierce +5%, Magic pierce +5%<br />Fiona - Magic pierce +3%, MaxMP +10%, Adds MATK +14% Delay -0.3 sec on Weapons.<br />Gerust - MATK +15%, Skill delay +1 sec, Adds MATK +5% on Weapons.<br />Dunkelis II - MATK +15%, Magic pierce +5% Adds MATK +5%, Magic up by Lv, Magic pierce +5% on Additional.<br />Tarna - MATK +10% Magic +100, Adds MATK 5% and Magic +400 on Additional.<br />Ushilth - Spell burst +1%. Skill delay -0.2 sec. Adds Skill delay -0.3s and MATK +12% on Additional.<br />Agira Jarma - MATK +12% Cast defense +5%, adds MATK +8% and INT +5 if equipped on Special.<br />Mezzaluna - MATK +15% MaxMP -40%, Adds MaxMP +40% on Special.<br /><br /><strong>Al Crystas</strong><br />Zazel - ATK +15 ATK +2% MATK +30 MATK +2%<br />Parazaia - MATK +20 MATK +3% Auto MP recovery +25%<br />Jusal - MATK +4% Water magic +4% Cast time -4%<br />Fiona (UNRELEASED) - MATK + 4% Magic Pierce + 5% MaxMP + 7%<br />Douin - MATK +2% Melee R +2%, Heal recovery +5%<br />Bergen - MATK +3% ATK -3%, Magic evasion +2%<br />Vatendeth - Melee R +10%, Magic R +10%, Hate rise -20%, Melee pierce +15%, Magic pierce +15%<br />Irai - MaxHP +3% Melee R +10% Heal Reward +5%<br /><br />Try to make pure blue and red lines, as these will increase your defense and magic defense overall with some additional HP and MP. You may end up getting some autoskill into the mix which may be undesirable but it can still work. However, if you do not care for magic defense go all for red.<br /><br /><strong>Relic Crystas<br /></strong>Bubbly Hat -&nbsp;Range cut +1%, Melee R +1%. Drop rate &amp; EXP gain +10% during Valentine's Day event.<br />Giorgio -&nbsp;Melee &amp; Magic R +2%<br />Memory Fragment -&nbsp;ATK&amp;MATK +10, DEF&amp;MDEF +10, MaxHP&amp;MP +10<br /><br /><br /><strong>Abilities - I would recommend the following:</strong><br />*HP<br />*Melee Defense<br />*Magic Defense<br />*Intelligence<br />*Vitality<br />*Rate Cut</span></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;">Evasion Set</span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><span style="color: #c0c53a;"><strong><u>Evasion Set</u></strong> - This set focuses on getting as much evasion as possible so that you can avoid getting hit by major attacks whilst dealing damage with ailments. I only recommend getting this set if you're AGI heavy, as you'll need every bit of Evasion possible to make this as viable as a choice.<br /><strong>Weapons</strong><br />Stardust Bow - Special Bow, ATK +20%, Critical Damage +17%, Absolute &amp; Magic Evasion +20%. (Hidden: ASPD Minimum)<br />Legacy of Will II - ATK +18%, MaxHP +15%, MaxMP +15%, Accuracy +15%, Evasion +20%, Melee pierce +18%, Item recovery +15%, ATK up by AGI.<br />Red Tengu IV - Evasion +16%, Critical damage +19%, ASPD -10%, Melee up based on STR, Small Melee pierce up by Lv.<br />Amber Sail IV - Magic attack chance by attack, Critical damage +12%, Evasion +40%, ASPD becomes lowest.<br />Mirror Rod AG -&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>Body Equipment</strong><br />Exelis (Strengthened x 3) - ATK +8% MATK +8% Evasion +15% Magic R +13% Skill delay -1.8 sec<br /><br /><strong>Additional Equipment</strong><br />Buckler (Strengthened x 2) - Melee R +6% Evasion +15% if DEX&gt;200, Counter on Evasion+5%.<br />Doggy Ears (Strengthened x 2) - Evasion +15%, MATK +6%, Autoskill +6%, Absolute evasion +10%, INT +5.<br />Itiance (Strengthened x 2) - MATK +12%, Heal recovery +6%, Ailment R+12% Evasion+15% Magic evasion +8% Light magic +4% Dark R +4%.<br />Red Bunny Ribbon - MaxHP up by Lv x5, Evasion +15%, Hate rise -10%.<br /><br /><strong>Special Equipment</strong><br />Douin's Talisman - Evasion +10%, Melee pierce +3%, Melee pierce up by DEX.<br />Strategy Ring - Accuracy +10%, Evasion +10%, Melee and Magic Pierce up by DEX (Hidden: Melee+200, ATK +6%, MATK +4%, Melee Pierce +5%) (Every 35 DEX = 1% Melee&amp;Magic Pierce)<br />Volk Shoes - Evasion +10%, Absolute evasion +2%<br /><br /><strong>Crystas</strong><br />Ocypete - Evasion +5%.<br />Himmel - Critical rate +10, Evasion +5%.<br />Strix - AGI +6, DEF -10%, Evasion +1%.<br /><br /><strong>Al Crystas</strong><br />Shelk - AGI +5, Evasion +15%, Absolute &amp; Magic evasion +5%, Counter on evasion +5%<br />Valtia - ATK +3% MATK -3%, Absolute evasion +2%.<br />Leviam - MaxMP +10%, Magic R +10%, Magic evasion +5%, Cast defense +5%.<br />Minela - DEX +5 Accuracy +30% Magic evasion +5%<br />Cerbera - ASPD +10%, Absolute evasion +5% Magic evasion +5%<br />Bernhardt -&nbsp;KO time - 1 sec, Critical damage +4%, Magic Evasion + 5%<br />Absolute Evasion I/II/III - Absolute Evasion +1/2/3%.<br />Magic Evasion I/II - Magic Evasion +1/2%.<br />Spikeleon - Magic Evasion&amp;Ailment R +10%, Melee and Magic change elements depending on the day.<br /><br /><strong>Relic Crystas</strong><br />Oswald - ATK +2% Absolute evasion +3%<br /><br />You wanna make one green line to get the most evasion possible, so get other colors and have solely 2 green al crystas.<br /><br /><strong>Abilities</strong><br />*Evasion<br />*Agility</span></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;">Counter Set</span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><span style="color: #da7e4b;"><strong><u>Counter Set</u></strong> - This set is focused towards a likewise direction in which the Resistance Set works. You basically rely on your autoskill to ensure that the counters are happening which can cancel out damage. It is an expensive set. However, this is very great for tanking and soloing bosses, here are the equips:<br /><strong>Weapons</strong><br />Genius - Special Sword MaxHP +30% Rate Cut +10% Melee &amp; Magic R+15% Counterattack chance by defense. (Cancel damage when counterattack activates)<br /><br /><strong>Body Equipment</strong><br />Dragon Mail (Strengthened x 2) - ATK +9%, MATK +10%, Critical rate +15, Critical damage +8%, Melee and Magic R +6%, Absolute accuracy +15%, Autoskill +5% (Hidden: Counterattack chance by defense (Cancel damage when counterattack activates))<br />Schwermer (Strengthened x 2) - Critical Damage + 16% Autoskill + 5% VIT + 9 Skill Delay - 1 sec, Counterattack chance by Defense. (Cancel damage when counterattack activates)<br /><br /><strong>Additional Equipment</strong><br />Blue Epaulettes - MATK +8% MaxMP +5% Skill delay -1 sec, Counter chance by Defense. (Cancel damage when counterattack activates)<br />Ensis Shield - VIT +8 Reflect +10% Melee +300 Counter Chance by Defense (Cancel damage when counterattack activates)<br />Luna Epaulettes - MATK + 8%, Light R + 3% skill delay -1 sec. Counter Chance by Defense (Cancel damage when counterattack activates)<br /><br /><strong>Special Equipment</strong><br />Anything that has Autoskill, or these:<br />Mirage Stone - Damage cut by using MP, Unavailable if MP is not enough.<br />Azuki Charm - Damage cut +10% during Stun, Auto HP &amp; MP recovery +20%, Ailment R up by Lv.<br /><br /><strong>Crystas</strong><br />Frederico - Absolute &amp; Magic Evasion +2% INT +5 MATK +10%. When equipped in weapon, Autoskill +7%. If DEX&gt;=250, Magic +1%.<br />Jahoel - Absolute evasion +3%, Autoskill +3%, Adds Autoskill +3% on Special.<br />Rudolf - When equipped on Additional, MaxHP +15% Hate rise +10% MaxMP -20%, Autoskills +5% Range +1.<br />Praldy - Magic R +6%, Autoskill +3%, Adds Spell burst +10% on Armor.<br />Pole - INT +5 Autoskill +3%, Adds Spell burst +10% and Autoskill +2% on Additional.<br /><br /><strong>Al Crystas</strong><br />Any MATK +% or Melee/Magic R +% Al Crysta helps.<br />Halios - Autoskill +5% Hate rise +20% ASPD +20%<br />Sauro II - Melee +3% to all elements, All magic +3%, Delay -0.5 sec, Autoskill +2%<br /><br />I absolutely recommend mixing red and blue al crystas to make purple lines to get more autoskill for this set.<br /><br /><strong>Abilities</strong><br />*Autoskill on all equipment. This is a must to have constant disabling in damage.</span></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;">What Mobs to Hunt?</span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><span style="font-family: 'times new roman';"><span style="font-size: x-large;"><span style="color: #03a2b8;">Any mob is okay since Alchemists have an array of AoE spells to use at their disposal. Bosses that have no resistance to ailments are great for Alchemist as well.&nbsp;<a href="http://www.iruna-online.info/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">Iruna Online Info</a>&nbsp;is a great place to check for mobs (Go to Zones section and check individual areas.)</span><br /></span></span></div>
